'''Helen Lewis''' (born 1983) is a British [[journalist]] and the deputy [[editor]] of the ''[[New Statesman]]''.<ref>[http://www.newstatesman.com/page/contact-us "Contact Us"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404121037/http://www.newstatesman.com/page/contact-us |date=4 April 2013 }}, ''New Statesman'' website</ref> A [[left wing politics|left wing]], [[Third-wave feminism|third-wave]] [[Feminism|feminist]], she has also written for ''[[The Guardian]]''<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/profile/helen-lewis-hasteley Helen Lewis] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215212409/https://www.theguardian.com/profile/helen-lewis-hasteley |date=15 February 2017 }}, contributor page, guardian.co.uk</ref> and ''[[The Sunday Times]]''.
==Life and career== Lewis read English at [[St Peter's College, Oxford]], and after graduating, gained a Post-Graduate Diploma in Newspaper Journalism from London's [[City University London|City University]]. Subsequently, she was accepted on the ''[[Daily Mail]]'''s programme for trainee sub-editors, working in the job for a few years, and later joining the team responsible for commissioning features for the newspaper.
For five years from August 2006,<ref name="Lewis0112">Helen Lewis-Hasteley [https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2012/jan/10/secret-of-networking-talking "The secret of networking? Talking"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020045040/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2012/jan/10/secret-of-networking-talking |date=20 October 2016 }}, ''The Guardian'', 10 January 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.pressgazette.co.uk/node/38645 "Schmooze and Booze celebrates first birthday"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203013313/http://www.pressgazette.co.uk/node/38645 |date=3 December 2013 }}, ''Press Gazette'', 28 August 2007</ref> Lewis ran a networking scheme, open to all young journalists, called Schmooze and Booze, for which she organised events held in a Central London pub every other month.<ref name="Lewis0112"/> Lewis commented in 2007 that older colleagues, who had worked with each other for quite a long time, all seemed to know each other, while her contemporaries did not.<ref>[http://www.pressgazette.co.uk/node/37956 "Plenty of schmoozing and plenty of boozing"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202221644/http://www.pressgazette.co.uk/node/37956 |date=2 December 2013 }}, ''Press Gazette'', 13 June 2007</ref>
Lewis was appointed as Deputy Editor of the ''New Statesman'' in May 2012,<ref>'Media Monkey' [https://www.theguardian.com/media/mediamonkeyblog/2012/may/27/media-monkey-diary "Media Monkey: Warren Buffett, a BSkyB buffet, and Danny Cohen"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160927174914/https://www.theguardian.com/media/mediamonkeyblog/2012/may/27/media-monkey-diary |date=27 September 2016 }}, guardian.co.uk, 27 May 2013</ref> after becoming Assistant Editor in 2010.<ref>[http://www.newstatesman.com/media/media/2012/05/new-appointments-and-web-expansion "New appointments and web expansion"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130605155449/http://www.newstatesman.com/media/media/2012/05/new-appointments-and-web-expansion |date=5 June 2013 }}, newstatesman.com, 16 May 2012</ref> She is married to the journalist Jonathan Haynes.<ref>{{cite news|last=Urwin|first=Rosamund|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/health/boxing-clever-why-everyone-from-gigi-hadid-to-ellie-goulding-is-toning-up-in-the-ring-a2414631.html|title=Boxing clever: why everyone from Gigi Hadid to Ellie Goulding is toning up in the ring|work=London Evening Standard|date=10 August 2015|accessdate=16 July 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821162742/http://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/health/boxing-clever-why-everyone-from-gigi-hadid-to-ellie-goulding-is-toning-up-in-the-ring-a2414631.html|archivedate=21 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
