lata 2018|work=MARCA Claro México|access-date=2018-11-25|language=es-MX}}</ref> |}
==Leyenda de Plata 1998== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata''(1998) |image=El Pantera.jpg |caption=[[Pantera (wrestler)|El Pantera]] (depicted in 2008), one of the participants in the first version of ''Leyenda de Plata'' |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=July 24, 1998 to July 31, 1998 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[Ruleta de la Muerte (1998)|Ruleta de la Muerte]]'' (1998) |nextevent=[[CMLL International Gran Prix#International Gran Prix 1998|International Gran Prix]] (1998) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=First |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 1999|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (1999) }} The first ever ''Leyenda de Plata'' tournament was held in 1998 from July 24 to July 31 in ''[[Arena Mexico]]'', [[Mexico City, Mexico]]. The tournament was held to commemorate the 15 year anniversary of [[El Santo]]'s death in 1983. Unlike later tournaments there was no final, instead El Santo's son, [[El Hijo del Santo]], faced the winner of the ''Cibernetico'' to determine the first winner. [[Scorpio Jr.]] won the ''cibernetico'', outlasting [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]], [[Shocker (wrestler)|Shocker]], [[Olímpico]], [[Pantera (wrestler)|Pantera]], [[El Felino]], [[Negro Casas]], [[Tony Rivera]], [[La Fiera]], [[Dr. Wagner Jr.]], [[Blue Panther]], [[Satánico]], [[Karloff Lagarde Jr.]], [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]], [[Último Guerrero]] and [[Violencia]]. Scorpio Jr. defeated El Hijo del Santo by count-out to win the ''Leyenda de Plata.<ref name=Plata1998/><ref name=Leyenda/><ref name="LdP1998">{{cite news | author = Box y Lucha staff | title = La Leyenda de Plata | work = Box y Lucha Magazine | pages= 3&ndash;5 | id = issue 2361 | date = August 4, 1998 | language = Spanish}}</ref><ref name="LeyendaSL">{{cite news | author = Ocampo, Jorge | title = La historia de la Leyenda! | work = Super Luchas | id = issue 271 | date = September 30, 2007| language = Spanish}}</ref> {{clear}}
==Leyenda de Plata 1999== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (1999) |image=Hijo del Santo.jpg |caption=[[El Hijo del Santo]], 1999 tournament winner and son of the man the tournament was in honor of |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=November 26, 1999 to December 2, 1999 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=[[CMLL 66th Anniversary Show]] |nextevent=''[[List of CMLL tag team tournaments#Copa de Arena Mexico 1999|Copa de Arena Mexico]]'' (1999) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 1998|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (1998) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2000|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2000) }} The qualifying ''Cibernetico'' took place on November 26, 1999 and saw El Hijo del Santo outlast a field of 15 other wrestlers including [[Antifaz (wrestler)|Antifaz del Norte]], [[Bestia Salvaje]], [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|BlacK warrior]], [[Blue Panther]], [[Emilio Charles Jr.]], [[El Felino]], [[Fuerza Guerrera]], [[Negro Casas]], [[Olímpico]], [[Rey Bucanero]], [[Satánico]], [[Tarzan Boy (wrestler)|Tarzan Boy]], [[Tony Rivera]], [[Último Guerrero]] and [[Zumbido]]. El Hijo del Santo only eliminated one wrestler in the match, Último Guerrero to qualify for the final. Like in 1998 the 1999 ''Leyenda de Plata'' cibernetico winner went straight to the final, a rematch from the 1998 tournament, only this time El Hijo del Santo defeated Scorpio Jr. to win the tournament named after his father.<ref name=Plata1999/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name="LdP1999">{{cite news | author = Box y Lucha staff | title = Segunda Leyenda de Plata | work = Box y Lucha Magazine | pages= 3&ndash;6 | id = issue 2432 | date = December 14, 1999 | language = Spanish}}</ref>
