==Leyenda de Plata 2000== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2000) |image= |tagline= |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=September 22, 2000 to October 6, 2000 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[Entre Torre Infernal]]'' |nextevent=[[CMLL 67th Anniversary Show]] |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 1999|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (1999) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2001|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2001) }} The third annual ''Leyenda de Plata'' started on September 22, 2000, with a 16-man ''tornero cibernetico''. Unlike in 1998 and 1999, CMLL added a semi-final match to the tournament as the last two wrestlers in the ''cibernetico'' would meet in a singles match the following week. The semi-finalsts were [[Dr. Wagner Jr.]] and [[Negro Casas]], outlasting [[Antifaz (wrestler)|Antifaz del Norte]], [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Astro Rey Jr.]], [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]], [[Blue Panther]], [[El Felino]], [[Fuerza Guerrera]], [[Olímpico]], [[Rey Bucanero]], [[Ephesto|Safari]], [[Satánico]], [[Scorpio Jr.]], [[Tarzan Boy (wrestler)|Tarzan Boy]] and [[Zumbido]]. The two survivors faced off in a singles match the following week, which Negro Casas won. On October 6, 2000, Negro Casas defeated El Hijo del Santo to win the 2000 ''Leyenda de Plata''.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2000/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name=Canoe2000>{{cite web | url=http://www.canoe.ca/SlamWrestlingInternational/mexico_timeline-can.html | title=SLAM! Wrestling International -- 2000: The Year-In-Review Mexico | accessdate=July 31, 2015 | work=Slam Wrestling! | publisher=Canoe.ca}}</ref> {{clear}}
==Leyenda de Plata 2001== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2001) |image=Dr-Wagner-Jr.jpg |caption=[[Dr. Wagner Jr.]], first person eliminated from the match along with [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]] |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=October 5, 2001 to October 19, 2001 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=[[CMLL 68th Anniversary Show]] |nextevent=''[[Sin Piedad (2001)|Sin Piedad]]'' (2001) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2000|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2000) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2002|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2002) }} The 2001 ''Leyenda de Plata'' was the fourth annual tournament and the first tournament to feature a [[Battle Royal]] to determine the two teams for the cibernetico. The first eight men eliminated from the battle royal would be one team and the remaining eight wrestlers would form the other team in the cibernetico match that followed immediately after the battle royal. Team "A" consisted of [[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]], [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]], [[Black Tiger III|Black Tiger]], [[Fuerza Guerrera]], [[Juventud Guerrera]], [[Dr. Wagner Jr.]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]] and [[Antonio Gómez Medina|Másacara Mágica]]. Team "B" consisted of [[Antifaz (wrestler)|Antifaz]], [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]], [[Blue Demon Jr.]], [[El Hijo del Santo]], [[El Felino]], [[Ricky Marvin]], [[Ephesto|Safari]] and [[Virus (wrestler)|Virus]]. The last two survivors were Black Warrior and Black Tiger III, both from Team "A". On October 12, 2001, Black Warrior and BlacK Tiger III faced off in a singles match that Black Warrior won. The [[narrative thread|storyline]] of the match was Black Tiger III turning ''Rudo'' ([[Heel (professional wrestling)|heel]] or "bad guy") while Black Warrior was turning ''Tecnico'' ([[Face (professional wrestling)|face]] or "good guy") during the course of the match. The following week Black Warrior's momentum helped him gain the victory over Negro Casas to win the 2001 ''Leyenda de Plata''.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2001/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name="LdP2001">{{cite news | author = Box y Lucha staff | title = Black Warrior Ganador! | work = Box y Lucha Magazine | pages= 3&ndash;6 | id = issue 2531 | date = November 11, 2001 | language = Spanish}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable sortable" !style="background: #e3e3e3;"|# !style="background: #e3e3e3;"|Eliminated !style="background: #e3e3e3;"|Eliminated by !style="background: #e3e3e3;"|Time |- |1 and 2 |[[Dr. Wagner Jr.]] and [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]] |Double disqualification |&nbsp; |- |3 |[[Ephesto|Safari]] |[[Antonio Gómez Medina|Másacara Mágica]] |&nbsp; |- |4 |[[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]] |[[Blue Demon Jr.]] |&nbsp; |- |5 |[[Antifaz (wrestler)|Antifaz del Nortre]] |[[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]] |&nbsp; |- |6 |Averno |[[El Felino]] |&nbsp; |- |7 |[[Virus (wrestler)|Virus]] |[[Silver King (wrestler)|Black Tiger III]] |&nbsp; |- |8 |Blue Demon Jr. |[[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]] |&nbsp; |- |9 |[[Juventud Guerrera]] |[[El Hijo del Santo]] |&nbsp; |- |10 |[[Ricky Marvin]] |Máscara Mágica |&nbsp; |- |11 |Máscara Mágica |El Hijo del Santo |&nbsp; |- |12 |El Felino |Black Tiger III |&nbsp; |- |13 |El Hijo del Santo |Black Warrior |&nbsp; |- |14 |'''Winners''' |Black Warrior, Black Tiger III |&nbsp; |} {{clear}}
==Leyenda de Plata 2002== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2002) |image=Volador-Jr.jpg |caption=[[Volador Jr.]], tournament participant |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=July 26, 2002 to August 9, 2002 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[List of CMLL tag team tournaments#Copa de Arena Mexico 2002|Copa de Arena Mexico]]'' (2002) |nextevent=[[CMLL 69th Anniversary Show]] |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2001|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2001) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2004|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2004) }} The ''cibernetico'' qualifier for the 2002 ''Leyenda de Plata'' took place on July 26, 2002 and once again saw two teams of eight face off to determine the semi-finalists. Team "A" consisted of [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]], [[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]], [[Blue Panther]], [[El Felino]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]], [[Ephesto|Safari]], [[Satánico]] and [[Virus (wrestler)|Virus]]. Team "B" was [[Black Tiger III|Black Tiger]], [[Fuerza Guerrera]], [[Rayman (wrestler)|Hombre Sin Nombre]], [[Negro Casas]], [[Olímpico]], [[Tony Rivera]], [[Violencia]] and [[Volador Jr.]]. The two semi-finalsts were El Felino and Black Tiger III, making Black Tiger the first wrestler to qualify for the semi-final more than once. On August 2, 2002 El Felino defeated Black Tiger in the semi-final and a week later he defeated Black Warrior to win the tournament.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2002/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name="LdP2002">{{cite news | author = Box y Lucha staff | title = 2002 Leyenda de Plata | work = Box y Lucha Magazine | pages= 3&ndash;5 | id = issue 2570 | date = August 8, 2002 | language = Spanish}}</ref>
