==Leyenda de Plata 2004== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2004) |image=Mephisto CMLL.jpg |caption=[[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]], tournament participant |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=July 16, 2004 to July 30, 2004 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[Aniversario de Arena México#48. Aniversario de Arena México|48. Aniversario de Arena México]]'' |nextevent=''[[CMLL Torneo Gran Alternativa#Gran Alternativa 2004|Gran Alternativa]]'' (2004) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2002|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2002) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2005|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2005) }} After not holding a ''Leyenda de Plata'' tournament in 2003, it returned in 2004 with the qualifying ''cibernetico'' being held on July 16, 2004.<ref name=Leyenda/> the teams were: "A", [[Alan Stone (wrestler)|Alan Stone]], [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]], [[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]], [[Misterioso Jr.]], [[Satánico]], [[Tarzan Boy (wrestler)|Tarzan Boy]] and [[Virus (wrestler)|Virus]]. Team "B", [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]], [[Perro Aguayo Jr.]], [[Emilio Charles Jr.]], [[Antonio Gómez Medina|Másacara Mágica]], [[Místico]], [[Negro Casas]], [[Super Crazy]] and [[Volador Jr.]]. The main storyline of the ''cibernetico'' was the building rivalry between Negro Casas and the recently ''rudo''-turned Perro Aguayo Jr. Aguayo cheated to eliminate Negro Casas and along with Atlantis were the last two surviving wrestlers. On July 23, 2004 Aguayo and Atlantis wrestled in a singles match, which unlike previous years was a "best of three falls" match, that actually went to four falls before Perro Aguayo Jr. won. A week later Perro Aguayo Jr. defeated El Felino, using the victory to further the storyline with Negro Casas, Felino's brother and corner-man for the night. Following his victory Perro Aguayo Jr. broke the plaque with El Santo's mask on it, claiming that the Aguayo's were the greatest family in wrestling, refusing to accept a trophy with El Santo's name on it.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2004/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name="LdP2004">{{cite news | author = Rivera, Miguel | title = Leyenda de Plata! | work = Super Luchas | id = issue 65 | date = August 8, 2004 | language = Spanish}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable sortable" !style="background: #e3e3e3;" width=5%|# !style="background: #e3e3e3;" width=40%|Eliminated !style="background: #e3e3e3;" width=40%|Eliminated by !style="background: #e3e3e3;" width=15%|Time |- |1 |[[Misterioso Jr.]] |[[Super Crazy]] |12:36 |- |2 |[[Emilio Charles Jr.]] |[[Satánico]] |14:18 |- |3 |[[Virus (wrestler)|Virus]] |[[Místico]] |17:01 |- |4 |[[Alan Stone (wrestler)|Alan Stone]] |[[Volador Jr.]] |18:00 |- |5 |[[Antonio Gómez Medina|Másacara Mágica]] |[[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]] |20:18 |- |6 |Satánico |[[Perro Aguayo Jr.]] |22:33 |- |7 |Super Crazy |[[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]] |24:07 |- |8 |Místico |[[Tarzan Boy (wrestler)|Tarzan Boy]] |25:28 |- |9 |Volador Jr. |Averno |26:42 |- |10 |Averno |[[Negro Casas]] |28:05 |- |11 |[[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]] |[[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]] |29:02 |- |12 |Tarzan Boy |Negro Casas |32:31 |- |13 |Negro Casas |Atlantis |34:34 |- |14 |'''Winners''' |Atlantis, Perro Aguayo Jr. |34:34 |} {{clear}}
==Leyenda de Plata 2005== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2005) |image=Gedo at BCW East Meets West.jpg |caption=[[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]], non-CMLL wrestler participating in the tournament |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=October 28, 2005 to November 11, 2005 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=[[CMLL International Gran Prix#International Gran Prix 2005|International Gran Prix (2005)]] |nextevent=''[[Juicio Final (2005)|Juicio Final]]'' (2005) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2004|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2004) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2006|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2006) }} The 2005 ''Leyenda de Plata'' is the only tournament to not feature the previous year's champion defending the trophy, playing off Aguayo's breaking of the trophy the previous year.<ref name=Leyenda/> The lack of defending champion forced CMLL to change the format of the ''Leyenda de Plata'' as they held two eight-man ''ciberneticos'' instead of one 16-man, with the winner of each cibernetico facing each other the following week. The two ''cibernetico'' format has been the standard tournament format for the ''Leyenda de Plata'' ever since 2005. The first cibernetico took place on October 28, 2005 and featured [[El Hijo del Santo]], [[Ephesto|Hombre Sin Nombre]], [[La Mascara (wrestler)|La Máscara]], [[Volador Jr.]], [[Misterioso Jr.]], [[Jado]], [[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]] and [[Negro Casas]]. The match came down to Hijo del Santo and Casas and initially ended in a double pin. After the match was restarted El Hijo del Santo won by submission. The second ''cibernetico'' took place on November 4 and saw [[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]] outlast a field that also included [[Místico]], [[Último Dragón]], [[Maximo (wrestler)|Máxmio]], [[El Sagrado]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]], Hijo de Pierroth and [[Gedo (wrestler)|Gedo]]. On November 11, 2005, Atlantis defeated El Hijo del Santo with help from his corner-man [[Último Guerrero]] to win the seventh ''Leyenda de Plata''.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2005/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name="LdP2005">{{cite news | author = Rivera, Miguel | title = Leyenda de Plata! | work = Super Luchas | id = issue 132 | date = November 20, 2005 | language = Spanish}}</ref>
