==Leyenda de Plata 2006== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2006) |image=LuchadorAtlantis.jpg |caption=[[Atlantis (wrestler)|Atlantis]], defending champion who lost in the finals |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=August 25, 2006 to September 15, 2006 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[CMLL Reyes del Aire#CMLL Reyes del Aire 2006|Reyes del Aire]]'' (2006) |nextevent=[[CMLL 73rd Anniversary Show]] |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2005|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2005) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2007|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2007) }} The 2006 ''Leyenda de Plata'' started on August 25, 2006 with the first of two eight-man ''cibernetico'' qualifying matches. The ''cibernetico'' saw [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|Black Warrior]] eliminate [[Rey Bucanero]] as the last man in a match that also included [[Heavy Metal (wrestler)|Heavy Metal]], Metro II, [[La Mascara (wrestler)|La Máscara]], [[Último Guerrero]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]] and [[Misterioso Jr.]]. With Black Warrior winning the first ''cibernetico'' it was not too surprising that [[Místico]] won the second ''cibernetico'' as the two had been involved with a long-running storyline feud throughout 2006. Místico outlasted [[Mr. Águila]], [[Negro Casas]], [[El Sagrado]], [[Volador Jr.]], [[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]] and [[Alex Koslov]]. The semi-final on September 8, 2006, saw Místico defeat Black Warrior, followed by a "mask vs. mask", ''[[Lucha libre#Luchas de Apuestas|Luchas de Apuesta]]'' challenge from Black Warrior that Místico accepted for the [[CMLL 73rd Anniversary Show]]. On September 15, 2006 Místico defeated Atlantis to win the ''Leyeda de Plata'', overcoming interference from Atlantis' corner-man Black Warrior. After the match Black Warrior stole the ''Leyenda de Plata'' trophy and ran off with it, furthering their feud.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2006/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name="LdP2006">{{cite news | author = Rivera, Miguel | title = Leyenda de Plata! | work = Super Luchas | id = issue 177 | date = October 1, 2006 | language = Spanish}}</ref>
