==Leyenda de Plata 2007== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2007) |image=Maximo-CMLL.jpg |caption=[[Maximo (wrestler)|Máxmio]], tournament participant |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=May 18, 2007 to July 8, 2007 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=[[CMLL International Gran Prix#International Gran Prix 2007|International Gran Prix (2007)]] |nextevent=''[[Torneo Gran Alternativa (2007)|Torneo Gran Alternativa]]'' (2007) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2006|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2006) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2008|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2008) }} The ninth ''Leyenda de Plata'' was held between May 18 and June 8, 2007. This was the first year that ''Leyenda de Plata'' was held without [[El Hijo del Santo]] working for CMLL, CMLL claimed that they owned the rights to promote the ''Leyenda de Plata'' and has promoted it without Hijo del Santo working for CMLL since then. The first ''Cibernetico'' took place on May 18, [[Perro Aguayo Jr.]] was originally scheduled to be part of the match, hinting at a very anticipated Aguayo vs. [[Místico]] match that had been building for a while. In the weeks leading up to the first ''cibernetico'' Perro Aguayo Jr. was injured and had to pull out of the match, he was replaced by fellow ''[[Los Perros del Mal]]'' member [[Mr. Águila]], who'd go on to win the qualifier over [[Negro Casas]], [[El Felino]], [[Tarzan Boy (wrestler)|Tarzan Boy]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]], [[Maximo (wrestler)|Máximo]], [[Alex Koslov]], [[Stuka Jr.]], [[Volador Jr.]] and [[Mictlán (wrestler)|Mictlán]]. On May 25, 2007 [[El Sagrado]] qualified for his first ever ''Leyenda'' semi-final as he outlasted [[Averno (wrestler)|Averno]], [[Ephesto]], [[Virus (wrestler)|virus]], [[El Texano Jr.]], [[Leono]], [[Loco Max]], [[Valiente (wrestler)|Valiente]], [[Heavy Metal (wrestler)|Heavy Metal]] and [[Black Warrior (wrestler)|BlacK Warrior]].<ref name="LdP2007-semi">{{cite web | url= http://superluchas.net/2007/06/02/resultados-arena-mexico-1-jun-07/ | title= resultados Arena Mexico (1 Jun 07) | author= | date= June 2, 2007 | accessdate= September 23, 2009 | publisher=''SuperLuchas'' Magazine | language=Spanish}}</ref> On June 1, 2007 Mr. Águila defeated El Sagrado to earn a spot in the final.<ref name="LdP2007-semi"/> On June 8, 2007 Místico became the first wrestler to not only win the tournament twice but also in back to back years as he defeated Mr. Águila. Following his victory Perro Aguayo Jr. attacked Místico furthering the storyline between the top ''tecnico'' and top ''rudo'' of the promotion.<ref name=Leyenda/><ref name=Plata2007/><ref name="LeyendaSL"/><ref name=LdP2007>{{cite web | url= http://superluchas.net/2007/06/09/resultados-arena-mexico-8-jun-07/ | title= resultados Arena Mexico (8 Jun 07) | author= | date= June 9, 2007 | accessdate= September 23, 2009 | publisher=''SuperLuchas'' Magazine | language=Spanish}}</ref>
