==Leyenda de Plata 2011== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2011) |image=Leyenda de Plata 2011.jpg |caption=Official poster for the finals, depicting [[Volador Jr.]] (left) and [[Jushin Thunder Liger]] (right) |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=September 23, 2011 to October 7, 2011 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=[[CMLL Universal Championship (2011)]] |nextevent=[[CMLL 78th Anniversary Show]] |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2008|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2008) |nextevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2013|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2013) }} After a two-year hiatus, the eleventh ''Leyenda de Plata'' was announced on September 13, 2011, as taking place from September 23 to October 7, 2011.<ref name=LdP2011Announced>{{cite web|url=http://cmll.com/noticias.htm#conferencia |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/61g5zyoN2?url=http://cmll.com/noticias.htm |title=¡Infierno en el Ring! 10 cabelleras en juego en jaula celebrando el 78 aniversario del Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre |archivedate=September 13, 2011 |date=September 13, 2011 |accessdate=September 13, 2011 |work=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |language=Spanish |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> With the winner of the three previous ''Leyenda de Plata'''s, [[Místico]], having signed a contract with [[WWE]] in January 2011, CMLL eliminated the final stage of the tournament, meaning that the winners of the ''ciberneticos'' qualified straight for the finals. The first ''cibernetico'' took place on September 23 and was won by [[Volador Jr.]], who outlasted [[Delta (wrestler)|Delta]], [[Guerrero Maya Jr.]], [[La Mascara (wrestler)|La Máscara]], [[Metal Blanco]], [[Palacio Negro]], [[Pólvora]], [[Puma King]], [[Shigeo Okumura]], [[Stuka Jr.]], [[Tiger (wrestler)|Tiger]] and [[Valiente (wrestler)|Valiente]].<ref name=Cibernetico1>{{cite web|url=http://lacatedraldelaluchalibre.blogspot.com/2011/09/atlantis-se-impone-al-ultimo-guerrero.html|title=Atlantis se impone al Último Guerrero - Volador Jr. quiere ser leyenda|date=2011-09-23|accessdate=2011-09-24|work=La Catedral de la Lucha Libre|language=Spanish}}</ref> The second ''cibernetico'' took place on September 30 at CMLL's [[CMLL 78th Anniversary Show|78th Anniversary Show]] and was won by [[Jushin Thunder Liger]], who outlasted [[Diamante (male wrestler)|Diamante]], [[Dragón Rojo Jr.]], [[Flash (wrestler)|Fuego]], [[Hijo del Signo]], [[Olímpico]], [[Máscara Dorada]], [[Mephisto (wrestler)|Mephisto]], [[Metro (wrestler)|Metro]], [[Rey Escorpión]], [[Sangre Azteca]] and [[Virus (wrestler)|Virus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-10-01/lyger-por-la-leyenda-de-plata |title=Lyger por la Leyenda de Plata |author=González, Fernando |date=2011-10-01 |accessdate=2011-10-01 |work=[[Récord]] |language=Spanish |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003204803/http://www.record.com.mx/luchalibre/2011-10-01/lyger-por-la-leyenda-de-plata |archivedate=October 3, 2011 }}</ref> On October 7, Volador Jr. defeated Jushin Thunder Liger to win the 2011 ''Leyenda de Plata''.<ref name=Plata2011/>
