==Leyenda de Plata 2014== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Leyenda de Plata'' (2014) |image=OlimpicoandSuperParka.jpg |caption=[[Olímpico]] (blue mask), 2014 tournament participant |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=December 20, 2013 to January 3, 2014 |attendance= |venue=[[Arena Mexico]] |city = [[Mexico City, Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=[[CMLL 80th Anniversary Show]] |nextevent=''[[La Copa Junior#La Copa Junior Tournament (2014)|La Copa Junior]]'' (2014) |event=''Leyenda de Plata |lastevent2=''[[Leyenda de Plata#Leyenda de Plata 2011|Leyenda de Plata]]'' (2011) |nextevent2=TBA }} After a two-year hiatus the ''Leyenda de Plata'' tournament returned in late 2013 with two qualifying ''[[Torneo cibernetico]]s'' and a final match between each elimination match winner. The first match took place on December 20, 2013, as part of CMLL's ''[[CMLL Super Viernes|Super Viernes]]'' show and was won by [[Titán (wrestler)|Titán]]. The second ''torneo'' was won by [[Negro Casas]] a week later. On January 3, Casas defeated Titán to win the tournament.<ref name=Plata2014/>
