'''Santrex''' was a [[Web hosting service|web hosting provider]] that specialised in [[bulletproof hosting]], hosting many [[cybercrime]] [[internet forum|forums]]. The service was registered in the [[Seychelles]] and once hosted the [[Darkode]] [[Hacker (computer security)|hacking]] forums<ref>{{cite news|last1=Krebs|first1=Brian|title=Conversations with a Bulletproof Hoster|url=http://krebsonsecurity.com/2013/05/conversations-with-a-bulletproof-hoster/|accessdate=2 August 2015|date=May 2013}}</ref> as well as the Italian [[Hacking Team]] security organisation's control server for the [[Carabinieri]].<ref name="ht">{{cite news|last1=Krebs|first1=Brian|title=Hacking Team Used Spammer Tricks to Resurrect Spy Network|url=http://krebsonsecurity.com/2015/07/hacking-team-used-spammer-tricks-to-resurrect-spy-network/|accessdate=2 August 2015|date=13 July 2015}}</ref>
At one point in the top three malicious hosts according to [[Google Safe Browsing|Google's Safe Browsing program]] for hosting [[malware]], the site closed in October 2013 after failing to pay its bills to its [[London]] based [[data centre]] provider.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Krebs|first1=Brian|title=‘Bulletproof’ Hoster Santrex Calls It Quits|url=http://krebsonsecurity.com/2013/10/bulletproof-hoster-santrex-calls-it-quits/|accessdate=2 August 2015|date=October 2013}}</ref> Following this closure, Hacking Team resorted to [[BGP hijacking]] to recover control of its [[Command and control (malware)|command and control]] servers.<ref name="ht" />
{{Internet-stub}}
